Diversity Leadership: Lowell McAdam, Verizon CommunicationsLowell C. McAdamChairman and CEOVerizon Communications
“Verizon is committed to continuously identifying and expanding effective business partnerships with diverse suppliers,” Lowell McAdam says on the company’s website. “These mutually beneficial relationships will allow us to provide superior service and excellent communications experiences for our customers, while broadening our reach in the competitive marketplace.”
As Chairman and CEO, McAdam signs off on executive compensation tied to diversity and is a visible supporter of diversity-and-inclusion initiatives. Prior to his current position, McAdam served as Verizon’s President and Chief Operating Officer and as President and CEO of Verizon Wireless.
McAdam began his career in 1983 with Pacific Bell. He has held numerous leadership roles in the industry, including President and CEO of PrimeCo Personal Communications, a joint venture of Bell Atlantic and Vodafone AirTouch, and Vice President, International Operations at AirTouch Communications.
He earned a bachelor’s degree in engineering from Cornell University, where he sits on the board of trustees. He also has an M.B.A. from the University of San Diego. He has been a licensed professional engineer since 1979 and spent six years in the U.S. Navy Civil Engineer Corps.
McAdam is a director of the National Academy Foundation and co-chair of the CEO Council on Health and Innovation. He is a past chairman of the board of CTIA-The Wireless Association.




 




